HW:
Please read the assigned paper and hand in your review BEFORE the class. 
The review should indicate at least TWO contribution and at least TWO weakness/questions of the assigned paper.
Note that, please send me your report in PLAIN TEXT format, i.e., no HTML/PDF/WORD attachments, and please indicate your student ID in the email subject.

Reading List/Paper assignment (HW submission records):


Network Measurements
    
Link Capacity
      
Constantinos Dovrolis, Parameswaran Ramanathan, and David Moore. What do packet dispersion techniques measure? Infocom 2001. [PDF]
      Rohit Kapoor, Ling-Jyh Chen, Li Lao, Mario Gerla, and M. Y. Sanadidi. CapProbe: A Simple and Accurate Capacity Estimation Technique. SIGCOMM 2004. [PDF]
      Ling-Jyh Chen, Tony Sun, Guang Yang, M. Y. Sanadidi, and Mario Gerla. End-to-end Asymmetric Link Capacity Estimation. IFIP Networking 2005, Waterloo, Ontario, Canada, 2005. [PDF]
      Anders Persson, Cesar A. C. Marcondes, Ling-Jyh Chen, M. Y. Sanadidi, and Mario Gerla. TCP Probe: A TCP with built-in Path Capacity Estimation. The 8th IEEE Global Internet Symposium (in conjunction with IEEE Infocom'05), Miami, USA, 2005. [PDF]
      
Available Bandwidth
      
M. Jain and Constantinos Dovrolis. Pathload: an available bandwidth estimation tool. PAM 2002. [PDF]
      Jacob Strauss, Dina Katabi, and Frans Kaashoek. A measurement study of available bandwidth estimation tools. IMC 2003. [PDF]
      Vinay J. Ribeiro, Rudolf H. Riedi, Richard G. Baraniuk, Jiri Navratil, and Les Cottrell. pathChirp: Efficient Available Bandwidth Estimation for Network Paths. PAM 2003. [PDF]
      Alok Shriram, Margaret Murray, Young Hyun, Nevil Brownlee, Andre Broido, Marina Fomenkov, and kc claffy. Comparison of Public End-to-end Bandwidth Estimation Tools on High-Speed Links. PAM 2005. [PDF]
      
System and Measurement Issues
      
Li Zhang, Zhen Liu, and Cathy Honghui Zia. Clock Synchronization Algorithms for Network Measurements. Infocom 2002. [PDF]
      Vern Paxson. Strategies for Sound Internet Measurement. IMC 2004. [PDF]
      
Trace Analysis
      
Augustin Chaintreau, Pan Hui, Jon Crowcroft, Christophe Diot, Richard Gass, and James Scott. Pocket switched networks: Real-world mobility and its consequences for opportunistic forwarding. University of Cambridge, Computer Laboratory, Tech. Rep. UCAM-CL-TR-617, February 2005. [PDF]
      

Delay Tolerant Networks
    
Kevin Fall. A Delay-Tolerant Network Architecture for Challenged Internets. SIGCOMM 2003. [PDF]
      Sushant Jain, Kevin Fall and Rabin Patra. Routing in a Delay Tolerant Networking. SIGCOMM 2004. [PDF]
      Sushant Jain, Rabin Patra and Kevin Fall. Wireless: Using redundancy to cope with failures in a delay tolerant network. SIGCOMM 2005. [PDF]
      Anders Lindgreny, Avri Doria and Olov Schel. Probabilistic Routing in Intermittently Connected Networks. SAPIR 2004. [PDF]
      Yong Wang and Margaret Martonosi. Erasure-coding based routing for opportunistic networks. WDTN 2005. [PDF]
      Joerg Widmer and Jean-Yves Le Boudec. Network Coding for Efficient Communication in Extreme Networks. WDTN 2005. [PDF]
    
Mesh Networks
    
Douglas S. J. De Couto, Daniel Aguayo, John Bicket, and Robert Morris. A High-Throughput Path Metric for Multi-Hop Wireless Routing. MobiCom 2003. [PDF]
      Richard Draves, Jitendra Padhye, and Brian Zill. Routing in Multi-radio, Multi-hop Wireless Mesh Networks. MobiCom 2004. [PDF]
      A Raniwala and Tzi-cker Chiueh. Architecture and Algorithms for an IEEE 802.11-based Multi-channel Wireless Mesh Network. Infocom 2005. [PDF]
      Dan Aguayo, John Bicket, Sanjit Biswas, and Robert Morris. Link-level Measurements from an 802.11b Mesh Network. SIGCOMM 2004. [PDF]
      John Bicket, Daniel Aguayo, Sanjit Biswas, and Robert Morris. Architecture and Evaluation of an Unplanned 802.11b Mesh Network. Mobicom 2005. [PDF]
      Sanjit Biswas and Robert Morris. ExOR: Opportunistic MultiHop Routing for Wireless Networks. SIGCOMM 2005. [PDF]
    
Peer to Peer Networks
    
Antony Rowstron and Peter Druschel. Pastry: Scalable, distributed object location and routing for large-scale peer-to-peer systems. Middleware 2001. [PDF]
      Ion Stoica, Robert Morris, David R. Karger, Frans Kaashoek, and Hari Balakrishnan. Chord: A Scalable Peer-to-peer Lookup Service for Internet Applications. SIGCOMM 2001. [PDF]
      S. Ratnasamy, R. Karp, and P. Francis, M. Handley, and S. Shenker. A Scalable Content-Addressable Network. SIGCOMM 2001. [PDF]
      Bram Cohen. Incentives Build Robustness in BitTorrent. P2PECOM 2003. [PDF]
      Nikitas Liogkas, Robert Nelson, Eddie Kohler, Lixia Zhang. Exploiting BitTorrent For Fun (But Not Profit). IPTPS 2006. [PDF]
    



 




